gs” -- t8 Facticity Only in the Light of Eternity -- t9 Another Suggestion on Thinking Heidegger and Whitehead -- t10 Heidegger and C.G. Jung on Wholeness as the Telos of the Human Being -- t11 Heidegger and C.G. Jung on “Opposites” -- t12 Heidegger and Melville -- t13 Heidegger and a Robert Frost Poem -- t14 The Unspeakable Mystery of All Things -- t15 A “Hermetic Saying” and the Hermetic Tradition -- t16 Heidegger and Walt Whitman -- t17 Heidegger and the Limit of Language – and Rumi -- t18 Thomas Aquinas, “God,” and the “Godhead of God” -- tAfterword -- tA Note on the Text and Heidegger’s: Gesamtausgabe -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn Heidegger’s Being: The Shimmering Unfolding, the eminent Heidegger scholar Richard Capobianco draws on many new texts and sources to highlight in fresh ways the beauty and spiritual resonance of Martin Heidegger’s thinking about Being. As in his earlier books, Capobianco offers a meditative path through Heidegger’s thought. He illuminates major motifs that are overlooked or set aside by most contemporary readings of Heidegger, amplifying these motifs in an original, heartfelt, and eloquent way. The book also offers a series of reflections that bring Heidegger’s thinking into close proximity to other thinkers and poets, including Alfred North Whitehead, C.G. Jung, Robert Frost, Walt Whitman, and Rumi. Heidegger’s Being: The Shimmering Unfolding is intended not only for dedicated students of Heidegger’s work but also for engaged general readers who wish to come to a deeper appreciation of his distinctive vision of Being.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aOntology. 0aPhilosophy, Moderny20th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh  a